Package: bantha
Title: Bayesian Network Thresholding Heuristic Algorithm (BANTHA)
Version: 0.1.22
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "David B.", family = "Dahl", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "dahl@stat.byu.edu", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8173-1547")),
    person(given = "Elissa", family = "Bailey", role = c("aut"), email = "elissafish@gmail.com"),
    person(given = "Daisy", family = "Harris", role = c("aut"), email = "dasharon14@gmail.com"),
    person(given = "Authors of the dependency Rust crates", role = "ctb", comment = "see inst/AUTHORS file for details"))
Description: The BANTHA algorithm is a greedy search method which can be used to estimate a Bayesian network by minimizing the expected generalized structural Hamming (GSH) loss based on posterior samples from the Bayesian network distribution. See Dahl, Bailey, Harris, Andros (2025) <https://dahl.byu.edu/papers/dahl_bailey_harris_andros.pdf>.
